The International African Youth Forum (IFJA), has already carried out several projects aligned with the vision of AEYA, focused on youth, peace, solidarity and empowerment. These projects were carried out thanks to internal fundraising, member contributions and local partnerships.

Among these initiatives, we can cite: 
- the Conference on Peace for Refugees (Brazzaville, September 21, 2021): raising awareness among young Central African, Democratic Congolese and Rwandan refugees residing in the Republic of Congo;
- the Mass of thanksgiving for peace “Kimia po na Congo” (Kinshasa, March 18, 2022): spiritual and civic mobilization of young people around peace in the DRC;
- Distribution of food to orphans (Brazzaville, December 23, 2022): humanitarian action in favor of vulnerable children;
- the International Secretariat Forum (FIS 2025) (Brazzaville, July 20–24, 2025): large pan-African gathering of young people around community entrepreneurship and civic leadership (11 countries took part: Congo, DRC, Gabon, Chad, Cameroon, Senegal, Mali, Ivory Coast, Guinea, Togo, France).

These projects directly affected several hundred young people (participants, beneficiaries, volunteers) and strengthened their civic engagement.

Although we have not yet benefited from institutional funding, we have acquired solid experience in project management through community fundraising and volunteer engagement. The support of AEYA would now make it possible to amplify these actions and increase their impact on African youth.

